  "prompt": "What are the branch options for 7k rank holders in manipal institute of technology entrance exam?",
  "response": "For students who achieve a rank around 7k in the Manipal Institute of Technology (MIT) entrance exam, the branch options can vary based on the yearly cutoff trends, which may fluctuate depending on the number of applicants, difficulty of the exam, and seat availability. Typically, with a rank of 7,000, you might have limited options compared to those with higher ranks. However, you could still get into some engineering branches. Here are some possibilities:\n\n1. **Civil Engineering**\n2. **Chemical Engineering**\n3. **Biotechnology**\n4. **Mechatronics Engineering**\n\nHigher-demand branches like Computer Science Engineering, Information Technology, Electronics and Communication Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, and Electrical and Electronics Engineering may have higher cutoff ranks, making them difficult to access at a rank of 7,000.\n\nIt is always a good idea to check the latest cutoff information for the specific year you are applying, as it can provide a more accurate depiction of the branch options available. Additionally, reaching out to the admissions office or checking their official website for updated information can help clarify your options.",
